From the start of 2015, new job-seekers under the age of 30 will have to wait up to six months before receiving unemployment benefits.

Further, they will then have to participate in at least 25 hours per week under Work for the Dole, to receive any payments for the next six months.

'The problem is structural but the government insists on using the language of demonising and blame to the very people who are suffering the affects of that structure,' Dr Falzon added.

A national day of action is planned by tertiary students to protest against the Work for the Dole changes and education overhaul.  

